PenguinMic ‚Äî Real‚ÄëTime Audio Recorder

---

Welcome to PenguinMic!
PenguinMic allows you to record, play, and share audio directly in PenguinMod.

---

How to Use
1Ô∏è‚É£ Start recording

Block: start recording

Starts capturing audio from your microphone.

Audio is stored as raw floats in memory.

If you‚Äôre already recording, this does nothing.

2Ô∏è‚É£ Stop recording

Block: stop recording

Stops recording audio.

Make sure to stop before playing or downloading your recording.

3Ô∏è‚É£ Play recording

Block: play recording

Plays back everything you recorded.

Must stop recording first before playback.

4Ô∏è‚É£ Play samples

Block: play samples [SAMPLES]

Plays an array of raw audio samples.

SAMPLES can be:

JSON array: [0.1, -0.2, 0.5]

CSV string: 0.1,-0.2,0.5

Scratch list converted to string

Samples should be in the range -1 to 1.

5Ô∏è‚É£ Mic sample reporter

Block: mic sample

Returns the latest single audio sample (float) from the mic in real time.

6Ô∏è‚É£ Get recorded data

Block: recorded data (json)

Returns your recording as a JSON array of floats.

Can be used with play samples() or shared between projects.

7Ô∏è‚É£ Recording length

Block: recording length (samples)

Returns the number of audio samples in your current recording.

8Ô∏è‚É£ Clear recording

Block: clear recording

Clears the internal recording buffer, freeing memory.

9Ô∏è‚É£ Set max recording seconds

Block: set max recording seconds to [SECONDS]

Limits how long recordings can be (prevents huge memory usage).

Default is 30 seconds.

üîü Download WAV

Block: download recording (wav) [FILENAME]

Exports your recording as a 16‚Äëbit PCM WAV file.

Example: download recording (wav) "myvoice.wav"

Tips

For smooth playback, stop recording before calling play recording.

If you only want a short clip, consider setting max seconds lower to save memory.

Use get recorded data + play samples to share audio between projects.
